 AvTech User Registry System

A simple Java console-based application to register and manage users and their roles.
Built to reinforce Java fundamentals including OOP, immutability, and clean architecture.

---

 Features

- Register users with multiple roles
  -  List all registered users
  -  Search for users by name
  -  Follows:
    - Immutability principles
    - Encapsulation and access control
    - Defensive copying
    - Java Collections usage

---

Structure

AvTechUserRegistry/
├── src/
│   ├── Main.java
│   ├── Model/
│   │   └── User.java
│   ├── Database/
│   │   └── UserStore.java
│   └── Service/
│       └── UserService.java
├── .gitignore
└── README.md


    Technologies Used

- Java 17
- IntelliJ IDEA (or your IDE of choice)
- No frameworks — just pure Java

---

How to Run

1- Open in your IDE and navigate to src/Main.java

2- Run the program
    It will open a simple terminal-based menu system to interact with.


Sample Output:

Welcome to AvTech
1) Register
2) List Users
3) Find user by name
4) Exit

Enter Name:
    Jane Doe
Enter roles separated by a (comma):
    Admin, HR

User was successfully added!
